        <div class="newsTitle">
            <h1>What's New?</h1>
        </div>
      
        <section class="filter">
            <form>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="dateFilter">Date</label>
                    <input type="date" id="dateFilter" name="dateFilter" onchange="filterNews()">
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="genreFilter">Genre</label>
                    <input type="search" name="genreFilter" id="genreFilter" list="genreOptions" onfocus="loadGenres()" onkeyup="filterNews()" placeholder="Search by Genre">
                    <datalist id="genreOptions"></datalist>
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <button onclick="sortNewsBy('date')" class="sortByDateBtn" type="button"><i class="bi bi-calendar4-event"></i>Sort By Date</button>
                    <button onclick="sortNewsBy('genre')" class="sortByGenreBtn" type="button"><i class="bi bi-pen"></i>Sort By Genre</button>
                </div>
            </form>
        </section>

        <div id="newsCarousel" class="carousel slide" data-bs-ride="carousel">
            <div class="carousel-inner">
                <% if (news && news.length > 0) { %>
                    <% news.forEach((article, index) => { %>
                        <div class="carousel-item <%= index === 0 ? 'active' : '' %>">
                            <article class="d-block w-100">
                                <img src="/styles/imgs/news/logo-blackwhite.png" alt="News image" class="news-image">
                                <div class="article-footer">Last update: <%= article.date.toLocaleDateString() %> at <%= article.date.toLocaleTimeString([], { hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit' }) %></div>
                                <div class="update_content">
                                    <h3><%= article.genre %></h3>
                                    <p><%= article.txt %></p>
                                </div>
                            </article>
                        </div>
                    <% }) %>
                <% } else { %>
                    <div class="carousel-item active">
                        <article class="d-block w-100">
                            <p>No news available</p>
                        </article>
                    </div>
                <% } %>
            </div>
            <button class="carousel-control-prev" type="button" data-bs-target="#newsCarousel" data-bs-slide="prev">
                <span class="carousel-control-prev-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="visually-hidden">Previous</span>
            </button>
            <button class="carousel-control-next" type="button" data-bs-target="#newsCarousel" data-bs-slide="next">
                <span class="carousel-control-next-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
                <span class="visually-hidden">Next</span>
            </button>
        </div>
        <div class="api_articles">
            <section class="news">
                <h2>Latest Articles</h2>
                <article>
                    <h3>Real Madrid Clinches La Liga Title with Dominant Performance</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid secured their 35th La Liga title with a dominant performance against Villarreal,
                        winning 3-1 at the Santiago Bernabeu. Goals from Karim Benzema, Luka Modric, and Marco
                        Asensio sealed the victory for Zinedine Zidane's side.</p>
                    <p>The win caps off an impressive season for Real Madrid, who have been in scintillating form
                        throughout the campaign. With the La Liga title secured, attention now turns to the UEFA
                        Champions League final where Real Madrid will face off against Liverpool.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Published on: May 12, 2024 | By: John Smith</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>Injury Update: Eden Hazard Ruled Out for Remainder of Season</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid forward Eden Hazard has been ruled out for the remainder of the season after
                        suffering a hamstring injury in training. The Belgian international has struggled with
                        injuries since joining Real Madrid and this latest setback comes as a blow to both the
                        player and the club.</p>
                    <p>Manager Zinedine Zidane expressed his disappointment at the news, stating, "Eden is an
                        important player for us and it's unfortunate to lose him at this stage of the season.
                        However, we have a strong squad and I'm confident that other players will step up in his
                        absence."</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Published on: May 10, 2024 | By: Sarah Johnson</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>Zinedine Zidane Extends Contract with Real Madrid</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid have announced that manager Zinedine Zidane has signed a contract extension,
                        keeping him at the club until 2026. Zidane, who returned to Real Madrid for a second spell
                        in 2019, has enjoyed tremendous success during his tenure, winning multiple La Liga and
                        Champions League titles.</p>
                    <p>The news comes as a boost for Real Madrid fans, who hold Zidane in high regard for his
                        achievements both as a player and a manager. Under Zidane's guidance, Real Madrid have
                        remained one of the dominant forces in European football.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Published on: May 8, 2024 | By: David Jones</p>
                </article>
            </section>

            <section class="results">
                <h2>Latest Results</h2>
                <article>
                    <h3>Champions League Final: Real Madrid 2 - 1 Liverpool</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid secured their 14th UEFA Champions League title with a hard-fought 2-1 victory
                        over Liverpool in the final. Goals from Vinicius Junior and Sergio Ramos helped Real Madrid
                        overcome an early deficit and clinch the trophy.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Date: May 8, 2024</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>La Liga Match: Real Madrid 3 - 0 Barcelona</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid delivered a statement victory over rivals Barcelona with a convincing 3-0 win in
                        the latest La Liga fixture. Goals from Karim Benzema, Toni Kroos, and Marco Asensio ensured
                        a comfortable victory for Zinedine Zidane's side.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Date: May 5, 2024</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>Copa del Rey Final: Real Madrid 4 - 2 Atletico Madrid</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid lifted the Copa del Rey trophy after a thrilling 4-2 victory over city rivals
                        Atletico Madrid in the final. Goals from Karim Benzema, Eden Hazard, Luka Modric, and Marco
                        Asensio secured the win for Zinedine Zidane's side.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Date: May 1, 2024</p>
                </article>

                <article>
                    <h3>Champions League Semi-Final: Real Madrid 3 - 0 Bayern Munich</h3>
                    <p>Real Madrid booked their place in the UEFA Champions League final with a resounding 3-0 win
                        over Bayern Munich in the semi-final. Goals from Karim Benzema, Vinicius Junior, and Sergio
                        Ramos sealed the victory for Zinedine Zidane's side.</p>
                    <p class="footer1">Date: April 24, 2024</p>
                </article>
